
# Ecommerce Sites
Ecommerce site are used to collect site-level reviews.

## Ecommerce Site Object
Represents a ecommerce site object.

```json
{
  "id": "esite_8ekmxve4f3ep4in",
  "name": "example.com"
}
```

### Attributes
Field | Type | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
id | string | Unique identifier for the object.
name | string | Name for ecommerce site. In most cases, this would be the domain name.


## Retrieve Ecommerce Site

> Example Request

```shell
curl https://api.onvoard.com/v2/ecommerce-sites/esite_8ekmxve4f3ep4in \
-H 'X-API-Key: {API_KEY}'
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "id": "esite_8ekmxve4f3ep4in",
  "name": "example.com"
}
```

Retrieve ecommerce site with given ID.

### HTTP Request
`GET https://api.onvoard.com/v2/ecommerce-sites/:ecommerce_site_id`

### Returns
Ecommerce Site object if valid ID was provided.


## List all Ecommerce Sites

> Example Request

```shell
curl https://api.onvoard.com/v2/ecommerce-sites \
-H 'X-API-Key: {API_KEY}'
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "num_sites": 1,
  "num_pages": 1,
  "current_page": 1,
  "results": [{
    "id": "esite_8ekmxve4f3ep4in",
    "name": "example.com"
  }]
}
```

List all ecommerce sites user have access to.

### HTTP Request
`GET https://api.onvoard.com/v2/ecommerce-sites`

### Returns
List of ecommerce sites objects.

### Arguments
Field | Type | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
keyword | string | Filter by specific keyword.
page | integer | Traverse to specific page. Page index starts from `1`.
page_size | integer | Number of sites you want to return for each page. Can be from `1` to `100`. Default is `10`.



